      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Modern civilizations are characterized by complex, stratified social hierarchies and highly specialized labor, which is something that is largely absent in simpler, more \"primitive\" societies. These complex systems rely on abstract institutions, written laws, and vast, interconnected networks of trade and governance. In contrast, simpler structures tend to be small-scale, kinship-based, and governed by much more immediate, localized norms. The shift is essentially from small, homogenous groups to large, diverse, and bureaucratic entities.",
